Mediterranean
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4A359FFB8FF97A3A9F9F2FE416055" blockId="11.[151,1437,1554,1797]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFB8FF97A3A9F9F2FE9C61C9" bold="true" box="[151,256,1663,1689]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Remark.</emphasis>
Because of the similarity in distal lobe shape of the male aedeagus, we firstly considered this species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD8DAFFB8FF97A3F8F92EFD0461ED" authority="Delgado &amp; Jach, 2007" authorityName="Delgado &amp; Jach" authorityYear="2007" box="[198,664,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Ochthebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avdati">
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFB8FF97A3F8F92EFE0F61ED" box="[198,403,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Ochthebius avdati</emphasis>
Delgado &amp; Jäch, 2007
</taxonomicName>
. However, after reviewer recommendation, we decided to refer it as 
<subSubSection id="C301F0D2FFB8FF97A3F8F94AFE416055" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="description">
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD8DAFFB8FF97A3F8F94AFDDA61B1" authorityName="Reiche" authorityYear="1872" box="[198,582,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Ochthebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus" subGenus="Asiobates">
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFB8FF97A3F8F94AFEDA61B1" box="[198,326,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Ochthebius</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFB8FF97A268F94AFE5F61B1" box="[342,451,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Asiobates</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B96F7F4BFFB8FF97A2EDF94AFDDA61B1" box="[467,582,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gr, waiting for future studies with new material that will help as to ascertain its real taxonomic status.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
